<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Leonhard, Graf von Castell</head><p>Der Rat bittet um Auskunft über die Versammlung der fränkischen Ritterschaft wegen des neuen Zolls zu Franken.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_533" id="265v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_533_r1l16"><expan>H<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>Lıenhart<ex>en</ex></expan> Grafen vnd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l17"><expan>H<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> ʒu Caſtell </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_533_r1l18"><expan>Gnedıg<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan> wır haben <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> wıe etlıch <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> vnd dıe </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l19"><expan>Rıtterſch<ex>aft</ex></expan> in dem Lande ʒu <expan>frank<ex>en</ex></expan> . bey <expan>eınand<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>geweſ<ex>en</ex></expan> ſeyn / als von </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l21">des neẅen ʒolles 
<add><ab facs="#facs_533_r1l20"><expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab></add> den man <expan>Jm<ex>m</ex></expan> lande <expan>ʒufranke<ex>n</ex></expan> vnterſteen meynt </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l22">ʒu <expan>neme<ex>n</ex></expan> So ıſt auch ſuſt <expan>mang<ex>er</ex>ley</expan> rede bey vns von <expan>deſſ<ex>elben</ex></expan> neẅen </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l23">ʒolles <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> / <expan>Daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> <expan>bıtt<ex>en</ex></expan> wır eẅr gnade mıt ganʒem fleıſʒ . daʒ </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l24">vns eẅr gnade bey dıſem botten in gutem getrawen <expan>verſchr<ex>eiben</ex></expan> welle </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l25">als vıl <expan>eẅr<ex>er</ex></expan> edell gepüre / wıe <expan>dıeſ<ex>elben</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> vnd <expan>Rıtterſch<ex>aft</ex></expan>
<del rend="strikethrough"> dar </del></ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l26">
<add>ʒu <expan>franke<ex>n</ex></expan> / dar</add>umb von <expan>eınand<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>geſchaıd<ex>en</ex></expan> ſeyn vnd auch wıe es vmb <expan>denſ<ex>elben</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l27">neẅen ʒolle noch geſtalt ſey . Daran beweıſt Jr vns ſunder dank </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l28">neͣm gnade dıe wır vmb eẅr gnade <expan>wıllıkl<ex>ich</ex></expan> vnd <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>v<ex>er</ex>dıenen</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_533_r1l29">wellen <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>vıgı<ex>lia</ex></expan> <expan>ſymo<ex>n</ex>ıs</expan> et Jude // </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_533" id="265v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab><expan>H<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>Lienhart<ex>en</ex></expan>, grafen und
                            <expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> zu Castell </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Gnedig<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan>, wir haben <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan>,
                        wie etlich <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> und die <expan>rittersch<ex>aft</ex></expan>
                        in dem lande zu <expan>Frank<ex>en</ex></expan> bey
                            <expan>einand<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gewes<ex>en</ex></expan> seyn als von des newen zolles
                                    <add><expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan></add>, den man
                                <expan>im<ex>m</ex></expan> lande <expan>zu Franke<ex>n</ex></expan>
                        untersteen meynt zu <expan>neme<ex>n</ex></expan>, so ist auch sust
                                <expan>mang<ex>er</ex>ley</expan> rede bey uns von
                                <expan>dess<ex>elben</ex></expan> newen zolles
                            <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>. <expan>Daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan>
<expan>bitt<ex>en</ex></expan> wir ewr gnade mit ganzem fleisz, daz uns ewr
                        gnade bey disem botten in gutem getrawen
                            <expan>verschr<ex>eiben</ex></expan> welle, als vil
                                <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan> edell gepüre, wie
                                <expan>dies<ex>elben</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>ren</expan> und <expan>rittersch<ex>aft</ex></expan>
<add>zu <expan>Franke<ex>n</ex></expan> dar</add>umb von
                                <expan>einand<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>geschaid<ex>en</ex></expan> seyn und auch wie es umb
                                <expan>dens<ex>elben</ex></expan> newen zolle noch gestalt sey.
                        Daran beweist ir uns sunder dank neͣm gnade, die wir umb ewr gnade
                                <expan>willikl<ex>ich</ex></expan> und <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>v<ex>er</ex>dienen</expan> wellen. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>vigi<ex>lia</ex></expan>
<expan>Symo<ex>n</ex>is</expan> et Jude. </ab>
</div>
</div></body>
